      <section eId="sec_CCRP-954">
        <num>CCRP 954</num>
        <heading>954.  Jury pool; emergency sessions</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-954__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Upon motion by the district attorney and after a contradictory hearing, the court may summon jurors from the host jurisdiction.  The district attorney must show that the interests of justice are served by the approval of such motion.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCRP-954__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The summoning of jurors shall be conducted by the clerk of the host jurisdiction.  The cost of summoning jurors and all costs regarding jurors shall be paid by the affected court.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=330439</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
